<HEADLINE>
<P>
ZSA ZSA GABOR FOUND GUILTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The many judgments of Gabor seem to be made on her fame and wealth, and not on 
the evidence that she was beat and bruised by a so-called officer of the law. 
Witnesses corroborated her story and other citizens testified to similar 
experiences. 
</P>
<P>
Consequently, I think a critical issue was overlooked: that police abuse is a 
common occurrence and is conveniently passed off under the guise of the law. 
</P>
<P>
The message has been made clear that most people disapprove of Gabor for many 
reasons. When will the message be made clear that police abuse of generally 
law-abiding citizens is intolerable? In spite of her high profile, Zsa Zsa, I 
fear, is only the tip of the iceberg. 
</P>
<P>
WOODY McBREAIRTY 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
