<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAR STRIKES, KILLS WOMAN IN CROSSWALK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Van Nuys woman was struck and killed by a car Friday as she stepped off a 
curb at a Kester Avenue crosswalk, the Los Angeles Police Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
The woman, who was in her late 50s, died at Sherman Oaks Community Hospital 
about 30 minutes after the 7:05 p.m. accident in the 5400 block of Kester 
Avenue in Van Nuys, Sgt. Ray Lombardo said. Her name was withheld until 
relatives could be notified. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was hit by a car driven by a Van Nuys man in his early 30s as she 
began to cross Kester in the crosswalk, which did not have a stop sign or a 
traffic light, Lombardo said. The car, traveling south on Kester, was changing 
lanes to pass another car making a left turn when it hit the woman in the far 
right lane, he said. The driver's name was not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
The car did not appear to be speeding, Lombardo said, and the driver was not 
cited, pending an investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
