<HEADLINE>
<P>
THOUSAND OAKS TO MEET NATION'S TOP VOLLEYBALL TEAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Thousand Oaks High girls' volleyball team, undefeated and ranked No. 1 in 
the Southern Section 4-A Division, today will take on what Volleyball Monthly 
magazine calls the nation's best girls' volleyball tournament field of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
The 14th Invitational tournament, which begins pool play at 9 a.m. at UC Santa 
Barbara's Campus Events Center, features five of Volleyball Monthly's 
nationally ranked teams. 
</P>
<P>
Mira Costa, ranked No. 1 nationally, and second-ranked Clark High of Las Vegas 
are the favorites in the 25-team tournament. The other nationally-ranked teams 
include Corona del Mar (No. 4), Santa Barbara (No. 7) and Thousand Oaks (No. 
13). 
</P>
<P>
Pool play will be followed by a 16-team playoff at approximately 3:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The championship match is scheduled for 7 p.m. 
</P>
