<HEADLINE>
<P>
STUNT MAN BENEFIT TO BE HELD AT SAUGUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VINCE KOWALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saugus Speedway will be the site of the first Reid Rondell Stunt Foundation 
Charity Event with the running of today's Stunt Enduro 150. 
</P>
<P>
Kirstie Alley of the television program "Cheers" will play host to the event. 
Proceeds will benefit the families of stunt persons injured or killed in the 
line of work. Reid Rondell was a stunt man who was killed on the job. 
</P>
<P>
The event will feature 28 celebrities and stunt persons. Among those expected 
to participate are James Garner, Richard Dreyfuss, David Hasselhoff, Parker 
Stevenson and Carlos Palomino. 
</P>
<P>
The program will feature stunt shows, race exhibitions, stunt-group promotion 
booths, prizes and a celebrity race. 
</P>
<P>
Gates will open at noon and the celebrity race is scheduled for 6 p.m. A Stunt 
Spectacular, featuring a precision-driving exhibition and several daring stunts 
involving cars and motorcycles, will take place at 4 p.m. VINCE KOWALICK 
</P>
