<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALKER LANDS JOB AS PIERCE SOFTBALL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Karen Walker, a 22-year-old UCLA senior, has been hired to coach the Pierce 
College softball team, replacing John Skinner. 
</P>
<P>
A walk-on coach with no teaching responsibilities, Walker will continue to 
pursue her degree in kinesiology at UCLA while coaching the softball team. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm excited because I've always wanted to test coaching out and see if I 
wanted to do it," Walker said. 
</P>
<P>
Walker, a Woodland Hills native and former City Section co-Player of the Year 
at El Camino Real High, went on to become an All-Pacific 10 Conference player 
at UCLA and played on the gold-medal team in the U. S. Olympic Festival this 
summer. 
</P>
<P>
"She's got a very good track record," said Marian McWilliams, the Pierce 
athletic director. 
</P>
<P>
McWilliams interviewed several candidates for the position but said, "None of 
them really fit the bill like Karen did." 
</P>
</TEXT>
