<P>
NONLEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BARTLETT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bell-Jeff 14, South Pasadena 7 -- Bell-Jeff (1-3-1) gave up a touchdown on the 
first play from scrimmage, but fought back in the second half behind an Alfred 
Silva kickoff return for a touchdown and an Earl Matthews touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Silva took the opening kick of the second half and raced 86 yards for the 
score. On the first play from scrimmage in the fourth quarter, Matthews took an 
option pitch from quarterback Rod Chapman and scampered 75 yards untouched down 
the left sideline. MIKE BARTLETT 
</P>
