<TEXT>
<P>
Notre Dame 33, St. Bernard 6 -- Playing without star running back Errol Small, 
the Knights amassed 350 yards on offense and coasted to an easy victory over 
visiting St. Bernard (2-3). Small, who has scored nine touchdowns and is fourth 
in the Valley with 570 rushing yards, was sidelined because of a thigh 
contusion incurred in last week's loss to Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
Junior running back Fano Malieitulua filled in and rushed for 144 yards in 20 
carries and scored on a 28-yard pass reception and a three-yard run. Greg 
Andrachick completed six of 15 passes for 124 yards and two touchdowns for 
Notre Dame (4-1). BRYAN RODGERS 
