<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CURTISS LIFTS AGOURA TO TENNIS WIN OVER THOUSAND OAKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Natalie Curtiss of Agoura High defeated Tricia Shinden of Thousand Oaks in the 
final singles match Friday to clinch the Chargers' 10-8 nonleague tennis 
victory at Agoura. 
</P>
<P>
Leading, 8-7, Agoura (5-1) needed Curtiss' victory to win the match. Had 
Curtiss lost, the match would have ended in a 9-9 tie, and Thousand Oaks would 
have prevailed in the tiebreaker, the total number of games won. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura lost seven of nine singles matches, but the Chargers took eight of the 
nine doubles matches. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura's No. 1 doubles team of Jackie Yang and Kathy Fitzpatrick and the No. 2 
team of Sue Jean Lee and Jennifer Frizzelle were each 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
Sherry Bryster and Michelle Palmisano were each 3-0 in singles for Thousand 
Oaks (2-6). 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Providence d. Buckley, 15-6, 15-3, 15-5 -- Mellissa Pope drilled 10 kills and 
Beth Beals supported her with eight for host Providence (3-6, 2-3 in league 
play). 
</P>
<P>
Providence's Deanna Bocz recorded eight service aces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
