<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DEUKMEJIAN NAMES 2 TO SUPERIOR COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. George Deukmejian has appointed two new Superior Court judges in Los 
Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
The governor named Charles W. Stoll, 58, of Studio City, and Sandy R. Kriegler, 
39, of Sherman Oaks, to the Los Angeles County bench. 
</P>
<P>
Stoll, who fills a newly created position, has been an attorney in private 
practice for 25 years in Glendale. He also served as a deputy county counsel of 
Los Angeles from 1959 to 1963. 
</P>
<P>
Kriegler, who also fills a newly created position, has served as a Los Angeles 
County Municipal Court judge since 1985. Before that, he was a deputy state 
attorney general for 10 years. 
</P>
<P>
Superior Court judges earn $89,851 annually. The appointments do not require 
Senate confirmation. 
</P>
