<P>
YOUNG SHOOTING VICTIM IDENTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The victim of a fatal shooting in Mira Mesa was identified Friday as Barbara 
Pacheco, 13, a student at Challenger Junior High School, a deputy San Diego 
County coroner said. 
</P>
<P>
The girl was found dead about 4:30 p.m. Thursday, after police were summoned to 
a home in the 10800 block of Parkdale Drive, just around the corner from the 
school. The coroner's deputy said the girl died of a single shot in the face. 
</P>
<P>
Pacheco had been visiting a classmate, a 12-year-old boy, who authorities said 
placed a 911 call to the San Diego Police Department at 4:20 p.m., saying that 
a friend had been shot. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Friday that the homicide unit is investigating, although officials 
believe the gun was fired accidentally. 
</P>
