<P>
A.J. Foyt, who escaped serious injury in a crash earlier this week in 
Charlotte, N.C., said he doesn't remember the stock-car accident that knocked 
him unconscious. 
</P>
<P>
Foyt was released from Charlotte Memorial Hospital Friday and immediately left 
for his home in Houston. 
</P>
<P>
Before leaving, however, he said, "It's the first time I've had an accident 
where I don't remember what happened. . . . Whatever I hit, I hit real hard. I 
feel pretty rough right now, and my neck is pretty sore. It's all swollen up 
and bruised on the right side. I know it does hurt." 
