<TEXT>
<P>
Edmonton Oilers owner Peter Pocklington, who shocked the hockey world when he 
traded Wayne Gretzky to the Kings last year, lost much of his business empire 
when he defaulted on a government loan. 
</P>
<P>
The Alberta government announced it has taken over the Gainers Inc. 
meat-packing plants and other holdings of Pocklington after the company failed 
to make interest payments on a $5.1-million loan, part of a much larger 
government-aid package. 
</P>
