<TEXT>
<P>
The federal government has agreed to shoulder a greater-than-normal share of 
the financial burden for damage caused by Hurricane Hugo in South Carolina, the 
White House announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The federal government will pay 75% of all eligible costs up to $34 million, 
and above that amount it will pay all costs. 
</P>
