<HEADLINE>
<P>
KARATE TEACHER EXPECTED TO FACE MOLESTATION CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Dana Point karate instructor has been arrested on suspicion of sexually 
molesting two of his young male students, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's spokesman Lt. Richard J. Olson said Alfonceo Vito Gaunchii, 44, was 
arrested Thursday afternoon at his residence in the 24000 block of Sherwood 
Way, where he teaches about 40 karate students in his garage. 
</P>
<P>
Olson said Gaunchii is expected to face charges of one count of oral copulation 
and three counts of child molestation. All involve incidents that allegedly 
took place at Gaunchii's home, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
The two alleged victims are 12-year-old and 14-year-old boys, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
The investigation began after members of the sheriff's sex crimes unit learned 
about allegations involving the 14-year-old. That led to a court-approved 
warrant to search Gaunchii's house on Wednesday. Investigators say they found 
some evidence at the home to corroborate information from the 14-year-old, but 
would not elaborate. 
</P>
<P>
However, it was during this investigation that they learned about the 
12-year-old, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
Gaunchii was arrested Thursday afternoon without incident at his home, where 
two other youngsters were present for a karate class. 
</P>
</TEXT>
