<P>
GAHR ROLLS OVER SONORA DESPITE LEWIS' HEROICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Ryan Lewis threw two touchdown passes and kicked a field goal, but 
it wasn't enough as Sonora High School lost to host Gahr, 34-16, Friday night 
in Hanford Rants Stadium in Cerritos. 
</P>
<P>
Gahr's Al McGuire returned the opening kickoff 85 yards for a touchdown and 
later scored on a 50-yard run with a fumble recovery as Gahr won its first 
homecoming game in six years. 
</P>
<P>
Sonora was playing without four starters who were suspended earlier in the week 
by Principal Ken Stitcher for their role in a bench-clearing brawl last week 
against Brea-Olinda. 
