<HEADLINE>
<P>
DROWN'S 2 TOUCHDOWN PASSES RALLY LA MIRADA PAST KATELLA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICH GUIREMAND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Chad Drown recovered from a rough start to lead La Mirada High 
School to a 38-21 come-from-behind victory over Katella in a nonleague football 
game Friday at La Mirada. 
</P>
<P>
Drown missed on his first six passes as his team fell behind, 14-3. He 
completed 10 of his final 13 passes -- including two touchdowns to Eric 
DeLaCruz -- for La Mirada (4-1). Katella is 2-2-1. 
</P>
<P>
Drown's passing was complemented by running back Joe Fernandez, who gained 198 
yards in 24 carries, including touchdown runs of 15 and four yards. 
</P>
<P>
After two short touchdown runs by Katella quarterback Dennis Briggs gave the 
Knights a second-quarter lead, La Mirada scored twice in the final 2 1/2 
minutes to take a 17-14 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Fernandez cut the deficit to 14-10 on a 15-yard touchdown run with 2:28 left. 
Moments later, the Matadors' Jeff Potter recovered a Katella fumble at the 
losers' 36-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
Drown hit DeLaCruz with a 15-yard touchdown pass with 22 seconds left. RICH 
GUIREMAND 
</P>
</TEXT>
