<P>
BRIEFCASE: HOTELS/TOURISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Radisson Suite Hotel has opened in Fullerton. The 98-room hotel is located 
off the Orange Freeway at Nutwood Avenue. . . . The Disneyland Hotel has named 
Linda McCoy as director of travel industry sales. McCoy joined the 1,200-room 
hotel in March, 1984, and is responsible for all travel-industry related 
matters. . . . The Anaheim Hilton and Towers has added Brit Osgood as assistant 
director of its sports and fitness center. . . . Airport Coach of Anaheim has 
named Al Patten as general manager. Patten previously was manager for the 
western region of Avis Leasing Corp. Airport Coach runs ground transportation 
to and from airports in Orange County, Long Beach and Los Angeles. 
