<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: HOTELS/TOURISM; 
</P>
<P>
PASSENGER TRAFFIC UP 2.6% IN AUGUST FROM 1988 RATE DESPITE FEWER FLIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Airline passenger traffic at John Wayne Airport increased 2.6% in August 
compared to the same month last year. For the month, there were 432,646 
boardings and deplanements at the Orange County airport, compared to 421,788 in 
August, 1988. 
</P>
<P>
The passenger traffic was up despite a 7.2% decline in commercial airline 
flight operations -- takeoffs and landings. Commuter airline operations rose 
42.1% over August, 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Total aircraft operations declined 6.4% last month to 49,087, compared to the 
same period last year, when takeoffs and landings totaled 52,418. 
</P>
<P>
General aviation activity, which accounted for 83.7% of the total aircraft 
operations last month, slid 7.5% when compared to August, 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
